  {
    "user": "U0123H7JRDM",
    "type": "message",
    "ts": "1748503588.933639",
    "client_msg_id": "02c8593d-edf1-4754-b68f-f6f6c0638ef3",
    "text": "Hi,\n\nYesterdays awesome demo of Scrappy during the FoC meetup and the small \"one more thing\"-moment about integrating Scrappy with AI/LLMs, reminded me of posting something here about 2 of my own recent new side projects:\n\n- <https://ocif-generator.vercel.app> : generate OCIF files and view them as JSON/SVG/React-flow\n- <https://app.prompttoform.ai>  : generate complex forms and play with them in the preview and also view its structure in the flow tab using react-flow. The latter is especially handy when the form contains multiple steps and has decisions in them (because you can build decision tree's with this generator).\n\nBoth tools use structured output using json schema's for the llm's, which allows for a lot of control instead of just prompting and trying to get structured output via a text prompt. Both of these tools were coded using a lot of AI as well (using Cursor).\n\nThe OCIF-generator was demoed yesterday at localfirst-conf by one of the OCWG core members <@U018MHFH4HF>\n\nMy plan is to integrate both of the above with my own infinte canvas visual programming system: <https://codeflowcanvas.io>.\n\nCheck <https://canvasprotocol.org> for more info about OCIF.",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "thread_ts": "1748503588.933639",
    "reply_count": 9,
    "reply_users_count": 2,
    "latest_reply": "1748508349.104159",
    "reply_users": [
      "U0123H7JRDM",
      "U06SS0DHZD1"
    ],
    "is_locked": false,
    "subscribed": false,
    "blocks": [
      {
        "type": "rich_text",
        "block_id": "LcBeq",
        "elements": [
          {
            "type": "rich_text_section",
            "elements": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Hi,\n\nYesterdays awesome demo of Scrappy during the FoC meetup and the small \"one more thing\"-moment about integrating Scrappy with AI/LLMs, reminded me of posting something here about 2 of my own recent new side projects:\n\n- "
              },
              {
                "type": "link",
                "url": "https://ocif-generator.vercel.app"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " : generate OCIF files and view them as JSON/SVG/React-flow\n- "
              },
              {
                "type": "link",
                "url": "https://app.prompttoform.ai"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "  : generate complex forms and play with them in the preview and also view its structure in the flow tab using react-flow. The latter is especially handy when the form contains multiple steps and has decisions in them (because you can build decision tree's with this generator).\n\nBoth tools use structured output using json schema's for the llm's, which allows for a lot of control instead of just prompting and trying to get structured output via a text prompt. Both of these tools were coded using a lot of AI as well (using Cursor).\n\nThe OCIF-generator was demoed yesterday at localfirst-conf by one of the OCWG core members "
              },
              {
                "type": "user",
                "user_id": "U018MHFH4HF"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "\n\nMy plan is to integrate both of the above with my own infinte canvas visual programming system: "
              },
              {
                "type": "link",
                "url": "https://codeflowcanvas.io"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": ".\n\nCheck "
              },
              {
                "type": "link",
                "url": "https://canvasprotocol.org"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " for more info about OCIF."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "reactions": [
